RACE.RACE_TEXT: OAKLAWN PARK RACE 12 6F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 90000. FOR ARKANSAS BRED (WHICH QUALIFY UNDER RULES GOVERNING ARKANSAS-BREDS) MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUSIC MISTRESS away in good order, dueled up front in the two path, disposed of the other speed into the lane, well clear, maintained. DELTA MOON back off the pace and the inside, four out to five wide turn, rallied for the place, no threat to the winner. ALOHA BABY mid pack while racing off the the inside, three to four wide through the turn, advanced to be closest to the winner with a furlong remaining, could do little with that one late, caught for the place. ICONIC BONNET headed up the second flight two off the rail up the backstretch, steadied in some traffic late n the turn between horses, went evenly through the lane. NEXT THURSDAY bumped then clipped heels soon after the start, raced back, four to five wide into the lane, rallied to improve position. COUNT IT ALL JOY bothered, bumped early, back, came four wide into the lane, improved position without posing a serious threat. CASHMERE BABY behind the pace toward the inside, in traffic late in the turn and into the lane, steadied, went evenly through the stretch. BE MY HUCKLEBERRY bumped at the start, raced back and failed to menace. ZONGS IRISH FROST prompted the issue for a half in the three path, had little left for the last time. MELANIA T came in after the start, bothered a couple of inner rivals, remained always back. NGALA broke in good order, dueled inside, stopped after a half. PRINCESS HADLEY bumped at the start, in mid pack early while along the inside, steady fade. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY REGARDING THE EARLY RUNNING, NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
